class TabularDataset(Dataset):
    def __init__(self, X_data, y_data):
        self.X_data = X_data
        self.y_data = y_data
        
    def __getitem__(self, index):
        return self.X_data[index], self.y_data[index]
        
    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.X_data)

class NeuralNet(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_dim):
        super(NeuralNet, self).__init__()
        self.layer_1 = nn.Linear(input_dim, 128)
        self.layer_2 = nn.Linear(128, 64)
        self.layer_3 = nn.Linear(64, 32)
        self.layer_out = nn.Linear(32, 1)
        self.relu = nn.ReLU()
        
    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.relu(self.layer_1(x))
        x = self.relu(self.layer_2(x))
        x = self.relu(self.layer_3(x))
        x = self.layer_out(x)
        return x

def plot_predictions(y_true, y_pred, start_index, end_index):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.plot(y_true[start_index:end_index], label='True Values', color='blue')
    plt.plot(y_pred[start_index:end_index], label='Predicted Values', color='red', alpha=0.6)
    plt.title(f"Comparison of True vs Predicted Values (Index: {start_index} to {end_index})")
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

def make_past_generation_input(data):
    data_column_name = ['generation(D-6)', 'generation(D-5)', 'generation(D-4)', 'generation(D-3)', 'generation(D-2)', 'generation(D-1)', 'generation(target)']
    
    for j in range(7):
        generation_data = data['Generation'].tolist()
        sliced_generation_data = generation_data[24+j*24:]
        empty_value_merging_data = sliced_generation_data + [NaN for i in range(24+j*24)]
        data[data_column_name[j]] = empty_value_merging_data
        
    nan_drop_data = data.dropna(axis=0)
    output_data = nan_drop_data.rename(columns={'Generation' : 'generation(D-7)', 'generation(target)':'generation'})
    
    return output_data

Gen_history_data = make_past_generation_input(data)

features = Gen_history_data.drop(columns=["Time","Generation"])
target = Gen_history_data["Generation"]
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(features, target, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

scaler = StandardScaler()
X_train = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test = scaler.transform(X_test)

train_dataset = TabularDataset(torch.FloatTensor(X_train), torch.FloatTensor(y_train.to_numpy()))
test_dataset = TabularDataset(torch.FloatTensor(X_test), torch.FloatTensor(y_test.to_numpy()))


train_loader = DataLoader(dataset=train_dataset, batch_size=64)
test_loader = DataLoader(dataset=test_dataset, batch_size=1)

model = NeuralNet(X_train.shape[1])
criterion = nn.MSELoss()
optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)

epochs = 1000
for epoch in tqdm(range(epochs)):
    model.train()
    for X_batch, y_batch in train_loader:
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        y_pred = model(X_batch)
        loss = criterion(y_pred, y_batch.unsqueeze(1))
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

model.eval()
y_pred_list = []
with torch.no_grad():
    for X_batch, _ in test_loader:
        y_pred = model(X_batch)
        y_pred_list.append(y_pred.cpu().numpy())

y_pred_list = [a.squeeze().tolist() for a in y_pred_list]
